race.comment: MISS KARIS (2) settled near the tail then came with a well-timed run to score with a bit in hand last start over this distance at Forbes. This race doesn't look quite as tough so despite a significant hike in the weights she looks the testing material again. STAR STROKE (9) was handy enough on the corner but ran out of condition when resuming over this trip at Coonamble on Sunday. Big class drop today and the quick back-up is a good sign. Everything points to a much better run. ULTRA WHITE (11) resumed in a modest BM50 over this distance at Mudgee a fortnight ago and was denied narrowly. Fitter and should give another good account. ANAISA (6) will find this harder than her first-up placing at the picnics. One for the exotics punters. BARCOO RIVER (5) has been about the mark in two runs this prep and should feature again.
